gomodel:SYNGO_843  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" , "Rationale: Ultrastructural localization of NCX3 in the cerebral cortex and hippocampus. Preembedding immunoperoxidase and silver-enhanced immunogold procedures were used.\nFigure 6b: in CA3 stratum radiatum, several dendritic profiles contain clumps of immunoreactivity associated to microtubules, mitochondria and to plasmalemma.\n6c: immunogold labelling associated with the plasma membrane near the postsynaptic density in a dendrite.\n6d,e: labelled dendritic spines.\n\nTable 1 presents a quantification of the immunolabeling, and shows that the majority of NCX3 profiles the cerebral cortex and in hippocampus are in dendrites and spines.\n\nAntibody: 'a rabbit polyclonal IgG antibody generously provided by Dr.\nK.D. Philipson'. Figure 1 demonstrated antibody specificity in western blotting of hippocampus, heart and cortex homogenates in comparison with a recombinant protein produced in HEK cells. Strong WB signals with little cross-reactivity are a good indication for the antibody specificity.. Experimental description: 'Sprague-Dawley male adult albino rats (200-300 g) were used in these studies'" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_843" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

